      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRETEY ROYAL (9) bumped into one over 1920m at York most recently when beaten 2.1L. That figure stacks up there and Webster's 3kg claim comes in handy with no weight on her back. Can get the job done this time around. INFRASTRUCTURE (1) couldn't go on with it after working into the race on the turn at York 27 days ago, though she was off a break there. Blinkers go on for the first time now and Gray returns to the saddle. Can put in an improved performance. PRINCIPAL DEALER (10) is yet to break through in 10 runs. Finished seventh at her last appearance over 1920m at York on April 6 after she got a long way back in the run. Rates highly in this field and can turn things around. LAST MILE (5) was below his best last time when ninth over 1800m at Ascot, beaten 10 lengths. Looks well placed so expect a better run this time. HUNDRED YARDS (3) went close last time out and has to be included on the back of that effort.",
